\chapter{1888 4d. Issue} 

In July 1888 the only provisional stamp of the Virgin Islands made its appearance, when 2000 copies of the 1/- stamp of 1868, with the coloured border, were sent to Antigua to be hand-stamped in violet. The hand-stamp was applied separately to each stamp, and occassionally the surcharge appears doubled.

The issue appears to have been necessary owing to the supply of the 4d. stamps, sent out the year previously, becoming low, the consignment of the regular stamps probably having been a small one.

