In 1890, the Leeward Islands General Stamp Act of that year, provided the introduction of uniform postage stamps for the Leeward Islands generally, including the Virgin Islands, and, from that date, Leeward Islands stamps were used in the Virgin islands concurrently with the distinctive local stamps, which remained valid if postage originated in the Virgin Islands. The Leeward Islands stamps were used were the issues of 1890, the Jubilee issue of 1897, and the surcharges of 1902, and although the Virgin Islands resumed the issue of their special stamps in 1899, the general Leeward Islands were still valid and available at the Virgin islands Post Offices. Virgin islands postmarks are therefore often found on the Leeward Islands stamps.




